('data-literacy', 'grp-data-literacy', 1, 'topic', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Data Literacy', 'Read tables, fields, grain, joins, aggregations, filters, distributions, and caveats with confidence.', 'This node builds practical BI analyst capability in data literacy.', 'side', 'ph-bi-foundations', 1, 301, 2, 'beginner', 1, NULL, NULL, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/bi-analyst", "parentGroup": "grp-data-literacy"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Explain Data Literacy through data structure, validation, access patterns, and reliability trade-offs.", "Apply Data Literacy in a realistic business intelligence task.", "Identify trade-offs, risks, debugging signals, or quality checks related to the topic."]'::jsonb, '["Create or update notes explaining Data Literacy with a concrete example.", "Use the topic to produce a query, schema, validation note, or data-quality artifact.", "Record at least two decisions, risks, or validation checks that prove applied understanding."]'::jsonb),
